25. Request Validation Rules
- Require authentication for protected endpoints.
- Validate IDs as integers or UUIDs depending on implementation.
- Validate pagination values.
- Validate topic, chapter, and exam relations.
- Reject malformed or unsupported request payloads.

26. Pagination Format
Recommended query params:
- page
- limit
- sort
- order

Example:
GET /api/v1/questions?page=1&limit=20&sort=created_at&order=desc

27. Filtering Support
Common filters:
- exam_id.
- subject_id.
- chapter_id.
- topic_id.
- difficulty_level.
- status.
- language.
- search query.

28. Error Codes
Use consistent HTTP status codes:
- 200 for success.
- 201 for created.
- 400 for validation errors.
- 401 for unauthorized.
- 403 for forbidden.
- 404 for not found.
- 422 for business rule validation.
- 429 for rate limit exceeded.
- 500 for server errors.

29. Security Requirements
- Use secure token authentication.
- Protect all admin and moderator routes.
- Rate-limit login and AI endpoints.
- Sanitize input text.
- Prevent IDOR issues.
- Log sensitive actions.
- Apply file upload restrictions.

30. Caching Strategy
Cache:
- Exam lists.
- Syllabus trees.
- Popular content.
- Frequently searched terms.
- Test templates.
- Analytics summaries.

31. Queue Jobs
Use background jobs for:
- Email and push notifications.
- Search indexing.
- Analytics aggregation.
- AI requests where needed.
- Content moderation tasks.

32. Webhooks and Integrations
If future integrations are needed, support:
- Payment webhooks.
- SMS provider callbacks.
- Email delivery status.
- AI provider callbacks if applicable.

33. API Versioning Strategy
- Keep /api/v1 stable.
- Introduce /api/v2 only when breaking changes are needed.
- Avoid breaking existing mobile clients.
- Maintain backward compatibility during transition periods.

